 Upon investigation of the footage, it becomes clear that the same suspects are involved in multiple robberies. Screenshots of the footage shows one man in particular that was present during the robbery of Markham and Totalsports in O.R Tambo Street. A screenshot of the robbery at TotalSport. Note that the man in the red cap is also seen in the next image. The other two people in the photo are innocent bystanders. Footage shows the same man who robbed TotalSports, was also involved in the Markham robbery. Four businesses were robbed during the month of October: •The Touch of Gold Jewellery Store in the Middelburg Mall was targeted by three men on 18 October. •Totalsports in O.R Tambo Street was targeted by four armed men on 24 October. •Markham in O.R Tambo Street was robbed on 30 October. See screenshots below:  •Uncle George’s Cafe was robbed last week, where two civilians were shot and injured during the attack. Video footage of the Markham robbery is now available for viewing by the public. The Middelburg SAPS says that anyone with information that could lead to the identification and arrest of these men can contact Det. Const. Mahlangu on 013 249 1402.   Hawks members sent to jail for fraud WATCH: The Place of Refuge – Once a vibrant village, now a ghost town WATCH: Robbery caught on video, police looking for suspects Three counts of poaching in one week – and the toll keeps rising   • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za